  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Interest">
    <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/views/visitor#VisitorInterestShape"/>
    <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/meta#CatalogValueShape"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n4fe22ed198f04afa80b3c1f504fa15f5b25"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n4fe22ed198f04afa80b3c1f504fa15f5b26"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#ExtrinsicMode"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Kind"/>
    <rdfs:label>Interest</rdfs:label>
    <amtmeta:scopedBy rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/views/visitor"/>
    <rdfs:comment>Kind ⊑ gufo:ExtrinsicMode. Instances are concrete interest-aspects: each Interest inheres in one Person (its bearer, via gufo:inheresIn) and externally depends on one pc: topic (via gufo:externallyDependsOn). Anti-rigid — a Person acquires and loses Interest-aspects over time without losing Person-identity. Runtime topic value-space defined by visitor_view:VisitorInterestShape (bucket membership) plus amtmeta:CatalogValueShape (prefLabel-as-catalog).</rdfs:comment>
  </rdf:Description>
